President Biden addressed the National Infrastructure Advisory Council to discuss the importance of investing in secure and resilient infrastructure. He emphasized the need for infrastructure that can withstand 21st century challenges, such as climate change, cyberattacks, natural disasters, and foreign threats. The President highlighted the significance of quick power restoration, access to clean water, communication capabilities during disasters, and the detection and removal of cyber threats. He commended the council for their work in strengthening water infrastructure and expanding the use of electricity across the economy. President Biden also expressed his anticipation for the council's future projects.